article.headline: Toledo 81, Delaware 58
article.story: CAROLINA, Puerto Rico (AP) -- Sammy Villegas scored 14 points and Toledo took advantage of 28 turnovers to beat Delaware 81-58 in the San Juan Shootout tournament Tuesday. The Rockets (2-5) had 18 steals and scored 41 points off Delaware's turnovers. Toledo took an early double-digit lead, but Delaware (5-4) had a 12-0 run midway through the first half, led by nine points from Harding Nana, to pull within one with 6:05 left until the break. The Rockets countered with a 10-0 run to close the first half leading 41-27. Toledo opened the second half with an 11-0 run and never looked back. Villegas, a native Puerto Rican, was 2-of-5 from 3-point range. Keith Triplett had 10 points and five steals for Toledo, and reserve guard Keonta Howell had 15 points, mostly in the final minutes with the game secured. Nana led Delaware with a career-high 30 points and 11 rebounds -- and six turnovers. Raphael Madera added 16 points.
